latestPosts.caption:
Representing the Santhal tribe through my collection, Vasi. This work draws inspiration from the vibrant Baha festival of the Santhal community, a celebration of renewal and nature. At the heart of my collection is the traditional attire known as Panchi—a symbol of cultural identity. Vasi is a tribute to precious handloom traditions of the Santhal tribe. This collection breathes life into heritage textiles by reinterpreting them in modern silhouettes, much like the forest itself—ever-evolving yet deeply connected to its roots. 
Designer: @hembromkanchan
Photographer and creative director: @melanatedbitch

Lakmé Fashion Week 2025. Backstage was a wild mix of glam, chaos, and pure Bollywood energy. Think sequins, sharp silhouettes, last-minute glam squads, and models running everywhere before they change for the next show.
Felt like I was behind the scenes of a high-budget fashion film. Can’t get enough of this madness.
